{"id":1236925922,"question_id":43,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"1 month, 1 week","timestamp":1713566870,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"3 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1236925922/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Multiply Strings","memory":"42.2 MB","code":"public class Solution {\n    public String multiply(String num1, String num2) {\n        int m = num1.length(), n = num2.length();\n        int[] result = new int[m + n];\n        \n        for (int i = m - 1; i >= 0; i--) {\n            for (int j = n - 1; j >= 0; j--) {\n                int mul = (num1.charAt(i) - '0') * (num2.charAt(j) - '0');\n                int sum = mul + result[i + j + 1];\n                result[i + j] += sum / 10;\n                result[i + j + 1] = sum % 10;\n            }\n        }\n        \n        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();\n        for (int digit : result) {\n            if (!(sb.length() == 0 && digit == 0)) { // Skip leading zeros\n                sb.append(digit);\n            }\n        }\n        \n        return sb.length() == 0 ? \"0\" : sb.toString();\n    }\n\n}\n\n","compare_result":"","title_slug":"multiply-strings","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
